physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Gained a low-grade fever at 100°F upon arrival.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert, oriented, no acute distress. Sclera anicteric, muddiness of mucous membranes normal, oropharynx clear. Neck supple, JVP not elevated, no lymphadenopathy. Lungs clear bilaterally, no wheezes, rales, or ronchi. Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, normal S1 + S2, no murmurs, rubs, or gallops. Abdomen: Soft, tender to palpation diffusely, non-distended, bowel sounds present, no rebound tenderness or guarding, no organomegaly. GU: no foley. Extremities warm, well perfused, 2+ pulses, no clubbing, cyanosis, or edema.
